question regarding the bank reconciliation statement in the event that the proper adjusting enteries were not recorded on the bank reconciliation what would be the effects on the income statement and balance sheet thanks it all depends on what was not adjusted the balance per bank statement can be different from the bal per cash book for main reasons there are items in the bank statement which were not recorded in the cash book for e g bank charges and overdraft interest if these were not adjusted in the cash book then bank charges and overdraft interest expense in the income statement would be understated and the cash bal in the balance sheet would be overstated there are items in the cash book which are not in the bank statement for e g cheques deposited not cleared by the bank yet or cheques issued not presented by the payees these do not require adjustment and have no effect either on the income statement or balance sheet Credit card Personal finance Financial audit Bank Cheque Monetary policy Inflation Schabir Shaik Trial Money supply Income statement Accounting methods Tax Corporate finance Bank fraud Euro Money Mortgage Microeconomics Taxation in the United States Hyperinflation Double-entry book-keeping Mutual fund Automatic teller machine Asset Fractional-reserve banking Mergers and acquisitions Collateralized debt obligation Central bank Car handling Finance Cash flow statement Social Security (United States) Money creation EBITDA EFTPOS Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Octopus card Depreciation Reserve Bank of New Zealand Gold standard Internet fraud Islamic banking Warner Music Group FairTax 401(k) Compensation of employees Mortgage-backed security IAS 36: Impairment of Assets Citigroup Yellow Ribbon campaign (Fiji) United Kingdom corporation tax Hearsay Taxation in the Republic of Ireland Comorian franc Economy of Russia Debt Employee stock option Supply and demand Carburetor U.S. generally accepted accounting principles Security 